            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Cut",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Cut </h3><p>The cut of a diamond is essentially the shape of a diamond. The diamond cuts determine how well a diamond reflects light. A perfectly cut diamond sparkles brilliantly, making it appear larger and more radiant. Some popular cuts are round, emerald, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-oval\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"oval cut engagement \">oval cut engagement </a>rings. It is also important to know the cuts so that you choose the one best suited for you. For example, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/jewelry\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"emerald cut engagement rings\">emerald cut engagement rings</a> are for someone who appreciate understated luxury while a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-heart\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"heart shape diamond ring\">heart shape diamond ring</a> is for someone who wants to express an unmistakable statement of love while choosing an eye-catching design.</p><h3>Clarity </h3><p>Clarity refers to how clean or flawless the diamond is. Fewer inclusions or blemishes mean a clearer and more valuable stone. For engagement rings, a clarity grade of VS1–SI1 often offers the best balance of beauty and price.</p><h3>Color </h3><p>Diamonds are graded from D (colorless) to Z (light yellow or brown). The closer to colorless, the rarer and more valuable the diamond. A G–H color range is ideal for a stunning yet budget-friendly option. You can check the details of the clarity and the color in your GIA  diamond certification. </p><h3>Carat</h3><p>The most important factor for customers of top diamond jewellery is usually the carat, meaning the size of the diamond. However, bigger is not always better. Focus on size, but also on proportions and how well-cut the diamond is. </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ND9GCy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How To Personalize Your Engagement Ring ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How To Personalize Your Engagement Ring </h2><p>Engagement ring designs feel more personal when customized. It adds emotion and attaches a core memory to the ring. There are many ways you can make your engagement ring deeply personal and unique, such as by choosing a unique setting like a halo or a three-stone setting, instead of the classic round cut solitaire ring.</p><p>You can also add a meaningful phrase, date, initials, or symbols as an engraving on the inner or outer side of the band. This makes a ring truly personal and evokes an instant feeling of affection every time the  partner looks at the engraving. </p><p>To add a pop of color, go the extra mile with colored diamonds. Pink diamond rings have become a popular choice for celebrity engagement rings. You can get your exclusively designed rings with a colored diamond of your choice to give a distinctive touch. </p><p>One of the most sentimental ways to upgrade your engagement ring is to redesign an heirloom piece by giving it a modern twist.<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": "how",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
